ENTERPRISE CONTRIBUTOR LICENSE AGREEMENT
(E-CLA)
(Exclusive License + Assignment Option + Patent Grant + AI-Assisted
Contributions)
This Contributor License Agreement (“Agreement”) is entered into by:
“Project Owner”: [Legal Entity Name] (“Owner”)
“Contributor”: Any individual or entity submitting Contributions
By submitting a Contribution to any repository owned or controlled by the Owner, the
Contributor agrees to this Agreement.
1. DEFINITIONS
1.1 “Contribution”
“Contribution” means any submission to the Project, including but not limited to:
source code (including AI-assisted or AI-generated code submitted by Contributor)
documentation
design materials
configurations
bug reports or suggestions intended to be implemented
any derivative work thereof
1.2 “Submission”
Any form of delivery, including pull requests, commits, issues, patches, or other
communication.
1.3 “Project”
All repositories, services, and related intellectual property owned or controlled by the
Owner.
2. ACCEPTANCE MODEL (ZERO-TRUST CONTRIBUTION
FRAMEWORK)
2.1 The Project operates under a Zero-Trust Contribution Framework, meaning:
No Contribution is trusted, merged, or relied upon until explicitly accepted.
No rights are granted by default or implication.
All Contributions are treated as unverified inputs.
2.2 Acceptance occurs only when the Owner explicitly merges or integrates a
Contribution.
2.3 The Owner may reject Contributions at any time, for any reason, without obligation.
3. RIGHTS GRANTED BY CONTRIBUTOR
3.1 Copyright License (Primary Model)
Contributor hereby grants to Owner a:
perpetual
irrevocable
worldwide
exclusive
royalty-free
fully sublicensable
transferable
license to use, reproduce, modify, adapt, publish, distribute, publicly perform, and create
derivative works of the Contribution.
3.2 Optional Assignment (Where Enforceable)
To the extent permitted by law, Contributor assigns to Owner all right, title, and interest
in and to the Contribution.
Where assignment is not legally effective, the exclusive license in Section 3.1 shall apply
instead.
4. PATENT LICENSE
Contributor grants to Owner a:
perpetual
irrevocable
worldwide
royalty-free
sublicensable
